         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">12. ii. 96 ¶ My dear Baron, ¶  ¶ Standing arrangements exist with the various Custom-Houses within the Colonies for the admittance of ¶  ¶ our ¶  ¶ spirit-drums when sent for collecting ¶  ¶ purposes....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">96.02.12a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Robert Etheridge<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Jr</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">AMS [49/4], [Curators' private letter books, vol. 19, p. 142], Australian Museum Archives, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12. ii. 96</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Standing arrangements exist with the various Custom-Houses within the Colonies for the admittance of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>our<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>spirit-drums when sent for collecting<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>purposes. With regard to Port Moresby<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Papua<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>New<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Guinea.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a special letter was addressed to his Excellency the Administrator<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">at the time</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the spirit for Mr Fitzgerald<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>William Fitzgerald.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was forwarded, and we have reason to know that the drum will be handed to the latter,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">duty</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>free whenever he chooses to enquire for it. Indeed a letter has been received from the Government Secretary asking for instructions as to its disposal from the fact that it has not been taken out of bond by Mr. F. The G.S. has been asked to allow it to remain until April 30th<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp; if not claimed by that time to reship it to us.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With regard to my taking a prominent part in Mr F.'s 2d Expedn you must be misinformed. All that this Museum has done is to supply Mr. F. with certain collecting<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>material which is debited against him until he repays in specimens. This was the original transaction, but of his second Expedition I know nothing</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I am</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Faithfully yrs</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>R.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Etheridge</p>
         </div>
      </body>
